50|$|A sling psychrometer, {{which uses}} {{thermometers}} {{attached to a}} handle or length of rope and spun {{in the air for}} about one minute, is sometimes used for field measurements, but is being replaced by more convenient electronic sensors. A <b>whirling</b> <b>psychrometer</b> uses the same principle, but the two thermometers are fitted into a device that resembles a ratchet or football rattle.|$|E

